This paper deals with a problem of bandwidth sharing in cellular networks, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a learning algorithm to solve the problem, which involves optimization and control (cs.IT, cs.SY). The use of Markov decision process (MDP) and stochastic approximation also suggests a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI).
